Neutral: Human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccines, approved by regulatory agencies such as the FDA and EMA, are designed to prevent infections caused by certain types of HPV and are recommended for both males and females starting from the age of 11 or 12.
HPV vaccines are approved by health authorities such as the FDA and WHO to prevent infections from human papillomavirus, which can lead to cervical and other types of cancer.
